The Rolling Stones are an English rock band formed in London in 1962. The first 
settled line-up consisted of Brian Jones (guitar, harmonica), Ian Stewart (piano), 
Mick Jagger (lead vocals, harmonica), Keith Richards (guitar), Bill Wyman (bass) 
and Charlie Watts (drums).
